Huntsville.104\u2013128 South Side Square: 104–128 South Side Square is a block of historic commercial buildings in Huntsville, Alabama. The block, known as "Commercial Row" in the late 1800s, consists of fifteen two- and three-story buildings constructed between 1835 and 1912. 108, built in 1835 as a store for the Bell Factory textile mill, and 110, built in 1840, are the oldest buildings on the block but both have been extensively modified.
